8.22	Shrine_of_Bah%C3%A1'u'll%C3%A1h	Shrine of Bahá'u'lláh	The Shrine of Bahá'u'lláh, located in Bahjí near Acre, Israel, is the most holy place for Bahá'ís and represents their Qiblih, or direction of prayer. It contains the remains of Bahá'u'lláh and is near the spot where he died in the Mansion of Bahjí.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Shrine_of_Bah%C3%A1%E2%80%99u%E2%80%99ll%C3%A1h.jpg/220px-Shrine_of_Bah%C3%A1%E2%80%99u%E2%80%99ll%C3%A1h.jpg
